WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:02.930
Hi! Welcome to IT.

2
00:00:02.930 --> 00:00:09.630
We’re your source for help with your assigned equipment, network access, or software. 

3
00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:12.130
We can help you in a number of ways

4
00:00:12.130 --> 00:00:17.830
in-person, on the phone, and online.

5
00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:25.630
Our friendly, competent staff will make sure you have everything you need to be productive and efficient.

6
00:00:25.630 --> 00:00:28.130
Come on, let me show you around.

7
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:32.670
At Tech Place in the National Office,

8
00:00:32.670 --> 00:00:37.400
you can work directly with  IT Help Desk staff to quickly get answers.

9
00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:41.000
No appointment is necessary during normal business hours,

10
00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:46.870
Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. ET.

11
00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:52.970
Just sign-in when you arrive and the technician will work to resolve the issue for you.

12
00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:56.030
Sure, I can take a look at that keyboard for you.

13
00:00:57.830 --> 00:01:04.970
When visiting the Tech Place is not an option, you can also chat, click, or call the Help Desk.

14
00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:11.200
The chat function is available through Microsoft Lync using Help Desk as a contact. 

15
00:01:11.570 --> 00:01:17.870
A technician can even log into your computer remotely to troubleshoot during a chat if necessary.

16
00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:25.270
The Help Desk portal allows you to quickly submit a ticket or review knowledge base articles.

17
00:01:25.830 --> 00:01:28.600
If you want to speak to an agent directly,

18
00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:36.170
you can call the Help Desk at 888-925-2002 

19
00:01:36.170 --> 00:01:46.170
or x3- HELP Monday through Friday, from 7 a.m. until 8 p.m.  E.T.

20
00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:54.360
You can learn more about IT Services and get detailed instructions on how to use the AARP Help Desk Portal

21
00:01:54.360 --> 00:02:02.130
and Chat by clicking “ITS-At Your Service” under Key Resources on the InfoNet home page.

22
00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:09.600
AARP supports staff that need to work remotely on a regular basis or just occasionally.

23
00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:15.970
Making teleworking easy and accessible is our goal in cultivating a mobile workforce.

24
00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:23.000
When you work remotely you can access internal AARP applications including

25
00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:29.570
InfoNet, Share Net, Outlook, and the shared H and V Drives.

26
00:02:29.570 --> 00:02:37.870
See more in the “Working Remotely” section on the ITS – At Your Service on InfoNet.

27
00:02:38.630 --> 00:02:42.600
So, that’s really all you need to know about IT for now. 

28
00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:48.300
Technology will keep you productive, and we’ll keep your technology running smoothly. 

29
00:02:48.300 --> 00:02:51.400
And that’s the big picture of IT services.

30
00:02:52.900 --> 00:02:56.800
Close this window to return to the map to find your next clue.
